criteria.driver_alignment:
Represent — converted assumptions into a parameterized model and stored variables;
Implement — executed a base-case cash flow model and produced NPV/IRR/PI/payback outputs;
Validate/Evolve — ran sensitivity and WAC +/-2% scenario tests and produced graphs and interpretation; Reflect — produced a recommendation based on results.

Discover — student explicitly defines the 10-year project scope and required outputs;  
Represent/Implement — student parameterizes and constructs year 0–10 cash flows (depreciation schedule, WC, terminal value) and runs the base-case model;  
Validate/Reflect — student runs sensitivity tests, interprets payback vs. project life, and explains year‑10 WC recovery and terminal value effects.
